---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const effectiveDate = 'May 17, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | MindMotion"
  description="How MindMotion handles information collected through this website."
>
  <Nav />
  <main id="main">
    <PageHeader
      title="Privacy Policy"
      subtitle="How we handle information collected through this website."
      density="compact"
    />

    <Section density="compact">
      <p><strong>Effective:</strong> {effectiveDate}</p>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how MindMotion, Inc. ("MindMotion,"
        "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and discloses information when
        you visit https://mindmotion.ai (the "Site"). By using the Site you
        acknowledge that you have read and understood this Policy.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="Information We Collect">
      <p>
        <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> When you visit
        the Site, we use Cloudflare Web Analytics to record aggregate
        information about page visits. Cloudflare Web Analytics does not set
        tracking cookies and does not require visitor consent under GDPR or
        CCPA. The data collected is aggregate and anonymous; we cannot
        identify individual visitors from this data.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Information you provide.</strong> If you submit our contact
        form, we collect the information you choose to provide: your name,
        email address, organization, and the contents of your message.
        Submission of the form is voluntary.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scheduling information.</strong> If you book a meeting using
        a scheduling link we provide, the third-party scheduling service
        receives the booking information you supply, typically your name,
        email address, and selected time slot. This applies only when a
        scheduling link is in use.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="How We Use Information">
      <p>
        We use the information described above to respond to your inquiry, to
        understand aggregate site usage, and to maintain and improve the
        Site. We do not sell your information. We do not share your
        information with third parties for their marketing purposes.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="Third-Party Processors">
      <p>
        We use the following service providers, each of which processes
        information on our behalf in accordance with its own privacy
        practices and our instructions.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Cloudflare, Inc.</strong> provides anonymous, aggregate web
        analytics. No tracking cookies are set and no personal information
        is collected.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Web3Forms</strong> receives submissions from our contact form
        and forwards them to our internal inbox.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scheduling tool host.</strong> When a scheduling link is in
        use, the host of that tool processes booking information you supply.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="Cookies">
      <p>
        The Site sets no first-party tracking cookies. Cloudflare Web
        Analytics does not require cookies. No cookie consent banner is
        displayed because no consent is required under GDPR or CCPA. If we
        add features in the future that set cookies (for example,
        third-party embeds), we will add a consent mechanism at that time.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="Data Retention">
      <p>
        We retain contact-form submissions only as long as needed to respond
        to your inquiry and to maintain a reasonable internal record of
        prior correspondence, typically no longer than twelve months.
        Aggregate analytics data is retained per our analytics provider's
        standard retention policy.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="Your Rights">
      <p>
        If you are a resident of the European Union, the United Kingdom, or
        California, you may have rights under applicable law to access,
        correct, or delete information we hold about you, and to restrict or
        object to certain processing. To exercise these rights, please
        contact us through our <a href="/contact">contact form</a>. We do
        not publish a public email address; the contact form is our
        canonical channel for inquiries.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="Children's Privacy">
      <p>
        The Site is not directed to children under the age of 16, and we do
        not knowingly collect information from children. If we learn that we
        have collected information from a child, we will delete it
        promptly.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="Changes to This Policy">
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material
        changes will be reflected by an updated effective date at the top of
        this page. Your continued use of the Site after changes take effect
        constitutes acknowledgment of the updated Policy.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section density="compact" heading="Contact" class="!pb-14 md:!pb-24">
      <p>
        Questions about this Policy may be directed to us through our
        <a href="/contact">contact form</a>.
      </p>
    </Section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
